    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-23T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="579"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.19/200a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="12" xml:id="d579fn12">President Roosevelt was aboard the U. S. S. <hi
                            rend="italic">Houston</hi> on a Caribbean cruise, during which an
                        interview occurred between him and President Arias of Panama.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-23T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 23, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>We will greatly appreciate learning of any decisions you may have reached after
                    your talks with President Arias regarding the right of the Government of Panama
                    to engage in ship to shore radio service and giving Panama instead of our own
                    commissaries the opportunity within certain limits of furnishing food supplies
                    to ships transiting <pb facs="0657" n="591" xml:id="pg_591"/> the Canal. We have
                    held up negotiations with Panama pending receipt of word from you of your
                    decisions on these two points and any protracted delay in resuming conversations
                    with Panama may give rise to misunderstanding.</p>
                <p>Best regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
